frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Patient to be wet with a Liquid.
An Agent matches location with an Entity in order to fulfill some  Purpose.
A Total has a Part, either  as a member of an aggregate or as  a constituent part of a simple entity.
An Activity takes some Time_length to complete.
In a text, a Source_of_information is given that provides a reader of the text with further Information relevant to the text.
A Figure is located relative to a Ground location.
frameExamples: I ca n't remember how many times he <t>visited</t> ! DNI
In Densmore's days it was sometimes made of an old-fashioned man's celluloid collar (<t>cf.</t> Densmore 1943: 116).
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is a volitional animate being who causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to become wet.
The <fen>Liquid</fen> is a fluid or gas that permeates or covers the <fen>Patient</fen>.  It most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with.
The <fen>Patient</fen> takes up the <fen>Liquid</fen> through its pores or has the <fen>Liquid</fen> covering its surface.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of wetness.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> wets the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> wets the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The sentient entity that is temporarily with the <fen>Entity</fen> in order to fulfil some <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The physical entity that is permanently associated with entities or characteristics that the <fen>Agent</fen> wishes to use for some <fen>Purpose</fen>.  During the visit, the <fen>Agent</fen> matches location with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which a visit is made.
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen> during the visit.
A complex entity, either an aggregate or a unit, of which a <fen>Part</fen>,  a constituent or a component, is specified.
A component or constituent that is specified to form part of the <fen>Total</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Total</fen> includes the <fen>Part</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Total</fen> includes the <fen>Part</fen>.
The event which requires some <fen>Time_length</fen> for completion.
The amount of time required for the <fen>Activity</fen>.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Time_length</fen> from the norm.
The individual who performs the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Activity</fen> takes place.
The <fen>Source_of_information</fen> is referred to as a source of information related to the current text.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The <fen>Figures</fen> are items which mutually serve to identify the location of the other items.
The region within which a <fen>Figure</fen> might be found.  This role is exclusive of <fen>Figure</fen>, and is a reconstrual that is not possible with verb lexical units.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
